item.title: Need Help Putting Server Up To Webclient
item.dc:creator: @ponqueque ponqueque
item.description:
@ponqueque wrote:

First off, are you guys talking about port forwarding or making a web client?

Second, if your talking about portforwarding, you have to go on to your routers site, which you just type the default gateway in your internet browser and add the ports on there, then you go onto windows firewall and add a new rule for 43594 TCP.

The port may change depending on which one your rsps uses.
